name: NOTTE__START_SESSION
description: Starts a new browser session and returns a session ID. An existing session cannot provide a session ID during creation.

keep_alive.description: Optional parameter to keep the session alive beyond its timeout period.

screenshot.description: Optional parameter to request a screenshot during the session.

session_id.description: Optional parameter to specify a session ID. Session ID should not be provided when starting a new session.

session_timeout.description: Optional parameter to set a custom timeout for the session. Specify the timeout in minutes.

name: NOTTE__OBSERVE_PAGE
description: This endpoint observes the actions available on a given URL within the session's environment.

url.description: Required parameter to specify the URL to observe. The URL to analyze and fetch available actions.

keep_alive.description: Optional parameter to keep the session alive beyond its timeout period.

session_id.description: Optional parameter to specify the session ID. The session ID of the session within which the environment will be observed.

session_timeout.description: Optional parameter to set a custom timeout for the session. Specify the timeout in minutes.

name: NOTTE__SCRAPE_DATA
description: This endpoint scrapes data from a specified URL within the session's environment.

keep_alive.description: Optional parameter to keep the session alive beyond its timeout period.

screenshot.description: Optional parameter to request a screenshot of the scraped page.

session_id.description: Optional parameter to specify the session ID.

session_timeout.description: Optional parameter to set a custom timeout for the session. Specify the timeout in minutes.
